<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (EC) No 1435/98 of 29 June 1998 prohibiting imports of Atlantic blue-fin tuna (Thunnus thynnus) originating in Belize, Honduras, and Panama </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1435/98, millega keelatakse Belize'ist, Hondurasest ja Panamast p&auml;rit hariliku tuuni (Thunnus thynnus) importimine 29. juuni 1998 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 113 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 113, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas fishery resources, which are an exhaustible natural resource, must be protected in the interests of biological balances and global food security; </inglise>
<eesti> ammenduvate loodusvarade hulka kuuluvaid kalavarusid peab bioloogilise tasakaalu huvides ja &uuml;ldise toiduainetega kindlustatuse tagamiseks kaitsma; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Community recognises the authority and the responsibility of the competent international organisations for stocks fished in international waters, and actively encourages their action; whereas the Community therefore subscribes to the objectives fixed by the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tuna (ICCAT) and endorses the measures in its 1994 and 1996 recommendations aimed at ensuring the effectiveness of the blue-fin tuna conservation programme; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &Uuml;hendus tunnustab p&auml;devate rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonide volitusi ja vastutust rahvusvahelistest vetest p&uuml;&uuml;tavate kalavarude suhtes ning soodustab aktiivselt nende tegevust; &uuml;hendus toetab Rahvusvahelise Atlandi Tuunikala Kaitse Komisjoni (ICCAT) poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud eesm&auml;rke ja kinnitab oma 1994. ja 1995. aasta soovitustes esitatud meetmeid, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on tagada hariliku tuuni s&auml;ilitamise programmi t&otilde;husus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the European Community has become a Contracting Party to ICCAT, as from 14 November 1997, and is therefore bound to implement the measures in question; whereas implementation must be handled by the Community, which has sole competence in the matter; whereas overfishing of Atlantic blue-fin tuna caused ICCAT to adopt an action plan in 1994 to ensure the effectiveness of measures to conserve the species; whereas the stocks concerned cannot be managed effectively by the ICCAT contracting parties, whose fishermen are obliged to reduce their catches of Atlantic blue-fin tuna, unless all non-contracting parties cooperate with ICCAT and comply with its conservation and management measures; </inglise>
<eesti> Euroopa &Uuml;hendus on alates 14. novembrist 1997 ICCATi lepinguosaline ning seep&auml;rast kohustatud rakendama k&otilde;nealuseid meetmeid; rakendamise peab tagama &uuml;hendus, kellel on k&otilde;nealuses asjas ainup&auml;devus; hariliku tuuni &uuml;lep&uuml;&uuml;gi t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;ttis ICCAT 1994. aastal vastu tegevuskava k&otilde;nealuse liigi kaitse meetmete t&otilde;hususe tagamiseks; ICCATi lepinguosalised, kelle kalurid on kohustatud hariliku tuuni p&uuml;&uuml;ki v&auml;hendama, ei saa asjaomaseid varusid t&otilde;husalt majandada, kui lepinguv&auml;lised pooled ei &uuml;hine ICCATiga ega j&auml;rgi selle kaitse- ja majandamismeetmeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in 1995 ICCAT identified Belize, Honduras and Panama as countries whose vessels fish Atlantic blue-fin tuna in a manner prejudicial to the organisation's measures to conserve the species, substantiating its findings with data concerning catches, trade and the observation of vessels; </inglise>
<eesti> juba 1995. aastal pidas ICCAT, kes tegi oma j&auml;reldused p&uuml;&uuml;ki ja kauplemist k&auml;sitlevate andmete ning laevade vaatlemise p&otilde;hjal, Belize'i, Hondurast ja Panamat riikideks, kelle laevad p&uuml;&uuml;avad harilikku tuuni viisil, mis kahjustab meetmeid, mida see organisatsioon on v&otilde;tnud k&otilde;nealuse liigi kaitseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas ICCAT's attempts to encourage the three countries to comply with measures for the conservation and management of Atlantic blue-fin tuna have been to no avail; </inglise>
<eesti> ICCATi p&uuml;&uuml;e ergutada nimetatud kolme riiki j&auml;rgima hariliku tuuni kaitse- ja majandamismeetmeid on j&auml;&auml;nud tulutuks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas ICCAT has instructed the contracting parties to take appropriate measures to prohibit imports from Belize, Honduras and Panama of Atlantic blue-fin tuna products in any form; whereas this measure will be lifted as soon as it is established that the countries in question have brought their fishing practices into line with ICCAT's measures; whereas this measure must therefore be implemented by the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> ICCAT on andnud lepinguosalistele korralduse v&otilde;tta vajalikke meetmeid, et keelustada harilikust tuunist toodete mis tahes kujul importimise Belize'ist, Hondurasest ja Panamast; osutatud meetmed v&otilde;ib l&otilde;petada niipea, kui tehakse kindlaks, et k&otilde;nealused riigid on viinud oma kalap&uuml;&uuml;gitavad vastavusse ICCATi meetmetega; seep&auml;rast peab need meetmed rakendama &uuml;hendus; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas this measure is compatible with the Community's obligations under other international agreements, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolev meede on koosk&otilde;las teistest rahvusvahelistest kokkulepetest tulenevate &uuml;henduse kohustustega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The release for free circulation in the Community of Atlantic blue-fin tuna (Thunnus thynnus) of CN codes 0302 39 11, 0302 39 91, 0303 49 21, 0303 49 23, 0303 49 29, ex 0303 49 90, ex 0304 10 98, ex 0304 20 45, ex 0305 20 00, ex 0305 30 90, ex 0305 49 80, ex 0305 59 90, ex 0305 69 90, ex 1604 14 11, ex 1604 14 16, ex 1604 14 18 and ex 1604 20 70 originating in Belize, Honduras and Panama is hereby prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga keelatakse Belize'ist, Hondurasest ja Panamast p&auml;rit ning CN-koodide 0302 39 11, 0302 39 91, 0303 49 21, 0303 49 23, 0303 49 29, ex 0303 49 90, ex 0304 10 98, ex 0304 20 45, ex 0305 20 00, ex 0305 30 90, ex 0305 49 80, ex 0305 59 90, ex 0305 69 90, ex 1604 14 11, ex 1604 14 16, ex 1604 14 18 ja ex 1604 20 70 h&otilde;lmatud hariliku tuuni (Thunnus thynnus) laskmine vabasse ringlusse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The landing of products mentioned in paragraph 1 for the purposes of Community transit is hereby prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga keelatakse l&otilde;ikes 1 mainitud toodete lossimine &uuml;hendust l&auml;biva transiidi tarvis. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall not apply to quantities of the products referred to in Article 1(1) which can be shown to the satisfaction of the competent national authorities to have been under way to Community territory on the date of its entry into force and which are released for free circulation no later than fourteen days after that date. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust ei kohaldata artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 m&auml;rgitud toodete koguste suhtes, kui riigi p&auml;devat ametiasutust rahuldaval viisil saab t&otilde;estada, et need tooted olid k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumishetkel teel &uuml;henduse territooriumile ja lastakse vabasse ringlusse hiljemalt 14 p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel sellest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Luxembourg, 29 June 1998. </inglise>
